Enterprise password hashing for the command line.

Usage: hsh [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  hash         Hash a password and print the storable form to stdout
  verify       Verify a candidate password against a stored hash
  rehash       Verify, then mint a fresh hash under the current policy
  inspect      Pretty-print the algorithm + parameters of a stored hash
  calibrate    Calibrate KDF parameters to hit a wall-time target
  completions  Emit shell-completion scripts for the named shell
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --json     Emit machine-readable JSON instead of plain text
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
